TEXT -2008 1088 Left 2 ;Ensure you have the correct symbol and 'WS_Halfbridge.lib' in this circuit's directory or a defined library\n \nRight-click the symbol to edit advanced features in the Spiceline\n \nLevel: Complexity of the body diode. 1 = simple body diode, 2 = full third quadrant (Vgs, Tj) with no reverse recovery, 3 = full third quadrant with reverse recovery\nRp: parallel resistance to package inductance. Set to 1m for increased speed, but less accuracy\nThermals: Complexity of the thermal model. Thermals=1 uses a closed-loop thermal network, Thermals=0 uses a static temp defind at the Tj pins or by the global temperature\nBPC: Presence of baseplate capacitance or not. BPC=0 disables baseplate capacitance, BPC=1 enables baseplate capacitance\n \nRead provided documentation for full explanation on how to properly use the models
